cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the classification of histological cell nuclei using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) architecture. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of CNNs for classification also falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of publicly available datasets and experiments, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with medical image analysis, which can be considered a sub-domain of multimedia (cs.MM).
